22 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2890 of Title 63, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 17145 Page 1

1 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
2 Emergency Communications Act".
3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2891 of Title 63, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 As used in the Oklahoma Emergency Communications Act:
7 1. "Authority" means the Oklahoma Emergency Communications
8 Authority created in Section 3 of this act;
9 2. "FCC" means the Federal Communications Commission;
10 3. "Revolving fund" means the Oklahoma Emergency Communications
11 Authority Revolving Fund created in Section 6 of this act.
12 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2892 of Title 63, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. There is hereby created within the Department of Public
16 Safety the Oklahoma Emergency Communications Authority which shall
17 be the governing board providing oversight, development, and
18 regulation of state emergency communications systems.
19 B. The Authority shall be composed of the following fifteen
20 (15) members:
21 1. One member representing the Oklahoma Department of Public
22 Safety, to be appointed by the Commissioner of Public Safety;
23 2. One member representing the Oklahoma Department of
24 Transportation, to be appointed by the Secretary of Transportation;
Req. No. 17145 Page 2

1 3. One member representing forestry and state fire response, to
2 be appointed by the Commissioner of Agriculture;
3 4. One member representing the Office of Management and
4 Enterprise Services, to be appointed by the Chief Information
5 Officer;
6 5. One member representing the State Department of Health, to
7 be appointed by the State Commissioner of Health;
8 6. One member representing a statewide organization dedicated
9 to representing municipal law enforcement, to be appointed by the
10 President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate;
11 7. One member representing a statewide organization dedicated
12 to representing county law enforcement, to be appointed by the
13 Oklahoma Sheriffs' Association;
14 8. One member representing a statewide organization dedicated
15 to representing fire service, to be appointed by the Governor;
16 9. One member representing a statewide organization dedicated
17 to representing Oklahoma municipalities, to be appointed by the
18 Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives;
19 10. One member representing a statewide organization
20 representing Oklahoma county commissioners, to be appointed by the
21 Governor;
22 11. One member representing a statewide organization
23 representing radio communications, to be appointed by the President
24 Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate;
Req. No. 17145 Page 3

1 12. One member representing a statewide organization
2 representing emergency medical services, to be appointed by the
3 Governor;
4 13. One member representing a city or county that owns radio
5 infrastructure and allows state users to utilize the system for day-
6 to-day operations, to be appointed by the Speaker of the Oklahoma
7 House of Representatives;
8 14. The Oklahoma 9-1-1 Coordinator or his or her designee; and
9 15. One member representing the Inter-Tribal Council of the
10 Five Civilized Tribes, to be appointed by Governor.
11 C. Members may be removed for cause. Members shall serve at
12 the pleasure of their appointing authority and vacancies shall be
13 filled by the original appointing authority. Each Authority member
14 shall be reaffirmed every two (2) years from the date of
15 appointment.
16 D. Members shall receive no compensation for serving on the
17 Authority.
18 E. Eight (8) members of the Authority shall constitute a
19 quorum, and the vote of the majority of the Authority member seats
20 shall be necessary for any action to be taken by the Authority.
21 F. The Department of Public Safety shall provide a dedicated
22 resource to the Emergency Communications Authority to carry out the
23 goals of the Authority and help coordinate between state and local
24
Req. No. 17145 Page 4

1 publ ic safety agencies. The Authority and the Department of Public
2 Safety shall agree on the resource provided to the Authority.
3 G. The Authority shall elect a chair from its membership. The
4 Authority shall meet at least quarterly. However, the chair may
5 call a meeting of the Board as often as necessary to transact
6 business.
7 H. The Department of Public Safety shall provide staffing, a
8 proper meeting space, and any other such assistance as the Authority
9 may require.
10 I. The Authority shall be subject to the Oklahoma Open Records
11 Act and the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act.
12 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2893 of Title 63, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 The powers and duties of the Oklahoma Emergency Communications
16 Authority created in Section 3 of this act shall be to:
17 1. Approve or disapprove the dedicated resource provided by the
18 Department of Public Safety pursuant to subsection F of Section 3 of
19 this act by majority vote of the members;
20 2. Promulgate rules, through the authority of the Department of
21 Public Safety, as necessary to implement the provisions of the
22 Oklahoma Emergency Communications Act and for the governance and
23 operation of the Oklahoma Emergency Communications Authority;
24
Req. No. 17145 Page 5

1 3. Prepare grant solicitations for funding for the purposes of
2 assisting public agencies in joining a state-owned shared radio
3 system. This includes both infrastructure and radio subscribers;
4 4. Oversee state allocated funding and funding allocations
5 within the state and local public safety agencies for any radio
6 infrastructure;
7 5. Final approval of contracts necessary to administer and
8 maintain emergency radio systems owned by the State of Oklahoma;
9 6. Work in conjunction with all state and local public safety
10 agencies and the Oklahoma Department of Transportation to move all
11 funding, contracts, and personnel related to the state-owned radio
12 infrastructure, including communication tower infrastructure, to the
13 Department of Public Safety within two (2) years of the effective
14 date of this act;
15 7. Establish comprehensive user training for the state-owned
16 emergency radio systems;
17 8. Establish a strategic plan for the state emergency radio
18 systems to ensure optimal operability and interoperability for all
19 public safety responders in the state. The plan shall include, but
20 may not be limited to secondary public safety responders such as
21 employees of the Oklahoma Department of Transportation and schools;
22 9. Provide guidance to public agencies regarding emergency
23 radio communications;
24 10. Facilitate information-sharing among public agencies;
Req. No. 17145 Page 6

