17 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2895 of Title 63, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
21 for the Oklahoma Emergency Communications Authority to be designated
22 the "Oklahoma Emergency Communications Authority Revolving Fund".
23 The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year
24 limitations, and shall consist of all monies received from state
Req. No. 17145 Page 9

1 appr opriations. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are
2 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
3 Emergency Communications Authority, for the purpose of supporting
4 the administration of the Oklahoma Emergency Communications Act.
5 Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the
6 State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with the
7 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
8 approval and payment.
